description: The strike against pension reforms is now in its 29th day, making it France's longest since 1968.
title: France protests: Longest strike in decades stuck in deadlock
title_page: France protests: Longest strike in decades stuck in deadlock - BBC News
maintext: On Thursday, France's national rail operator SNCF said it expected up to half of high-speed trains to be cancelled; only one in four inter-city trains would be running, while regional rail services would also be badly affected with half of suburban trains cancelled and only a third of trains circulating in the Paris region.
